###
#
# 2.0.0 release
#
###

2011-09-22 16:54  owes

	* updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.alpha-1.9.21,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.alpha-2.0.0,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.i486-2.0.0,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.ppc-1.9.21,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.ppc-2.0.0,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.sparc-1.9.21,
	  updates/2.0.0/ROOTFILES.sparc-2.0.0: Rename rootfiles for update
	  to v2.0.0

2011-09-22 16:51  eoberlander

	* updates/2.0.0/setup: Change new upgrade version in setup script.

2011-09-22 15:30  owes

	* updates/2.0.0/information.xml: Put correct version in update
	  information file.

2011-09-22 15:27  owes

	* make.sh, updates/1.9.21, updates/2.0.0: Set version for next
	  update to 2.0.0

2011-09-22 15:22  owes

	* config/logrotate/logrotate.conf.FLASH, updates/1.9.21/setup:
	  Revert logrotate.conf for FLASH install. maxsize option does not
	  exist.
	  Using size will give trouble viewing the log for past dates, but
	  that cannot be helped.

2011-09-21 14:32  eoberlander

	* langs/es_ES/install.po, langs/es_ES/ipcop.po,
	  langs/fr_FR/ipcop.po, langs/list_progress,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Updates from Language
	  Database.

2011-09-21 06:25  owes

	* updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Add some missing pieces to update
	  information.

2011-09-21 05:05  owes

	* html/cgi-bin/credits.cgi, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21:
	  Add 'Delfin' to Spanish translators.

2011-09-21 04:52  owes

	* langs/es_ES/install.po, langs/es_ES/ipcop.po,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Spanish translation fixes.

2011-09-17 09:03  gespinasse

	* lfs/check_files: find PKG_NAME to match the file name
	  
	  Give PKG_NAME prefile to all produced log here
	  
	  Inside find, we don't need to use recursive -R option for
	  scanelf, this speed a bit the search
	  
	  Search for configure WARNING in a separate log, compilation
	  warning file is so big
	  
	  Add a TODO, I have some code to fill that, not yet really checked

2011-09-17 08:02  gespinasse

	* lfs/rrdtool, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Use our compilation timestamp
	  hack for rrdtool
	  Simplify rd_cv_ms_async=ok using that instruction on configure
	  directly
	  
	  Remove deprecated options fixing this warning
	  configure: WARNING: unrecognized options: --disable-libintl,
	  --enable-local-libpng, --enable-local-zlib, --enable-latin2
	  
	  We don't need to disable language we haven't build like lua and
	  ruby, only disabling tcl and python is enought
	  
	  I tested a Fedora hack that remove rpath from RRDs.so.
	  That work but I am unsure this is really needed, so that part
	  stay commented.
	  
	  rrtool is only include in update, so everyone will have the same
	  file with same timestamp

2011-09-16 15:46  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/cppunit, lfs/cppunit, lfs/squid, make.sh:
	  Add cppunit, nothing include
	  This allow us to run squid make check

2011-09-15 12:31  gespinasse

	* lfs/tzdata, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Upgrade tzdat to 2011j

2011-09-15 08:40  eoberlander

	* langs/el_GR/ipcop.po, langs/list_progress,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Updates from Language
	  Database (el_GR)

2011-09-14 20:10  gespinasse

	* lfs/squid, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Upgrade squid to 3.1.15
	  
	  Add a comment for ac_cv_func_tempnam=yes, without that,
	  compilation fail
	  Unclear why we need this, Gentoo don't use that with similar
	  hardening.

2011-09-14 19:41  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/usb-modeswitch-data,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Fix usb-modeswitch-data
	  rootfile and include correct list in update.
	  For some reason, I commited a broken rootfile

2011-09-14 14:45  owes

	* lfs/usb-modeswitch-data: Add Id keyword property

2011-09-14 12:36  gespinasse

	* updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Add usb-modeswitch-1.1.9-jimsh
	  and data-20110805 into update

2011-09-14 10:57  owes

	* lfs/apache, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Upgrade apache httpd to 2.2.21

2011-09-13 16:54  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/openswan: It appear ./make.sh check_files
	  don't know about files include by parent directory.
	  So include directly the files, and check_files will find from
	  which package the file come from.

2011-09-13 16:11  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/usb-modeswitch,
	  config/rootfiles/common/usb-modeswitch-data, lfs/usb-modeswitch,
	  lfs/usb-modeswitch-data, make.sh,
	  src/patches/usb-modeswitch-1.1.9-jimsh_default-if.patch,
	  src/patches/usb-modeswitch-data-20110805_gzip.patch: Split
	  usb-modeswitch and usb-modeswitch-data
	  Upgrade usb-modeswitch to 1.1.9 and use the jimsh flavor to gain
	  tcl support
	  
	  Upgrade usb-modeswitch-data to 20110805
	  
	  Add a default-if patch that fix an issue on some device and will
	  be include in next version
	  
	  Add a patch on my own that remove gzip timestamp on the packed
	  configuration file

2011-09-12 19:12  owes

	* html/cgi-bin/logsystem.cgi, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21:
	  As is the Login/Logout section does not log anything. This adds
	  the local logons, logons via SSH are logged in the SSH section.

2011-09-12 19:07  owes

	* src/misc-progs/emailhelper.c: Add the additional characters from
	  SVN commit 5786

2011-09-12 08:56  owes

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Reorganise license text.

2011-09-12 05:51  dotzball

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Re-format timeframe tests.

2011-09-11 12:29  eoberlander

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl: Add code for a corner case where
	  NEXT_SWITCH_HOUR/MINUTE would not be set correctly.

2011-09-11 08:01  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/coreutils, lfs/coreutils,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Upgrade coreutils to 8.13, that
	  fix minor issues in chown, chgrp, cp, printf
	  
	  Remove the -N on patching uname, we want an error if an issue
	  happen applying the patch
	  
	  The move on usr/lib/coreutils/libstdbuf.so to
	  usr/libexec/coreutils/libstdbuf.so is intentional to fix an issue
	  with a futur automake release.
	  Let us not care that much as we do not use that file.

2011-09-08 06:20  gespinasse

	* lfs/gdb: I was too slow to commit 7.3 upgrade.
	  During that time, 7.3 was replaced by 7.3a and 7.3.1 has been
	  released, so upgrade to 7.3.1.
	  
	  Only 28 failures with 7.3.1 when building from my debian v6
	  (squeeze). That should be good enought for us.

2011-09-07 19:41  dotzball

	* src/scripts/puzzleFwRules.pl,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Fix check(s) for timeframe rules.
	  
	  Fixes SF bug #3403666

2011-09-07 06:45  gespinasse

	* lfs/gdb: Upgrade gdb to 7.3.
	  This fix the test suite on more recent distrib (for example
	  switching from debian v5 lenny to v6 squeeze)
	  for reason I haven't identified. Without upgrade, test log is
	  full of ERROR: Couldn't send <> to GDB
	  
	  Core dump feature usage for gdb test suite need that you unplug
	  pipe to apport that most distrib have set.
	  Look in lfs/gdb if you are curious for an example how to do that.

2011-09-03 11:06  owes

	* src/rc.d/rc.pulsardsl, src/rc.d/rc.red,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Fix path used for
	  br2684ctl, fixes using pulsar DSL.
	  Tweak use of debugging in rc.pulsardsl.

2011-09-01 20:44  owes

	* lfs/apache, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml, updates/1.9.21/setup: Upgrade
	  apache to 2.2.20

2011-08-28 19:30  dotzball

	* html/cgi-bin/email.cgi, src/scripts/monitorTraffic.pl,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Check subject texts for non
	  allowed characters and use english text if there are some non
	  allowed characters found.

2011-08-24 15:59  owes

	* config/cfgroot/templates/test.de.tpl,
	  config/cfgroot/templates/warn-traffic.de.tpl,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Add German translated email
	  templates.

2011-08-24 15:04  owes

	* html/cgi-bin/proxy.cgi, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21:
	  cache was disabled when only RAM memory is used by proxy. Also
	  add maximum size for harddisk cache to avoid overflowing
	  /var/log.

2011-08-24 14:47  owes

	* src/rc.d/rc.firewall, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21: Move
	  IPsec marking before CUSTOMFORWARD, to make the IPsec marks
	  available for custom rules should an admin require it.

2011-08-24 08:20  owes

	* src/misc-progs/emailhelper.c: Add GPL license URL instead of FSF
	  address

2011-08-24 07:29  dotzball

	* src/misc-progs/emailhelper.c,
	  updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
	  updates/1.9.21/information.xml: Use utf-8 when sending system
	  email (traffic warning etc.) with emailhelper.

2011-08-21 19:41  eoberlander

	* langs/list_progress, langs/tr_TR/install.po,
	  langs/tr_TR/ipcop.po, updates/1.9.21/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.21,
