	  use same ()
	  By the way fcdsl compilation is broken actually.

2011-04-30 20:57  gespinasse

	* lfs/cairo: Remove 2 obsolete configure options.
	  
	  When cairo is recompiled, that goes wrong somewhere and fail
	  with:
	  
	  Making all in cairo-trace
	  make[5]: Entering directory
	  `/usr/src/cairo-1.10.2/util/cairo-trace'
	  CC libcairo_trace_la-trace.lo trace.c:4502: warning:
	  '_content_from_surface' defined but not used
	  CC libcairo_trace_la-lookup-symbol.lo
	  CCLD libcairo-trace.la /usr/bin/ld: warning: creating a
	  DT_TEXTREL in a shared object. collect2: ld returned 1 exit
	  status
	  make[5]: *** [libcairo-trace.la] Error 1
	  
	  Using make V=1
	  libtool: link: gcc -shared .libs/libcairo_trace_la-trace.o
	  .libs/libcairo_trace_la-lookup-symbol.o -lpthread -lz -ldl
	  /usr/lib/libbfd.a -lm -march=i486 -mtune=pentium
	  -Wl,--hash-style=gnu -Wl,-soname -Wl,libcairo-trace.so.0 -o
	  .libs/libcairo-trace.so.0.0.0
	  
	  The libbfd.a may be the issue, the line before try to use
	  -lpthread -lz -ldl -lbfd -lm
	  
	  For now, use the temporary workaround to disable cairo trace,
	  that part will not be recompiled and the issue disappear.
	  
	  We should try to disable more cairo parts later.

2011-04-30 20:43  gespinasse

	* lfs/fontconfig: If fonconfig is recompiled, when
	  /etc/fonts/fonts.conf exist, file is move to a .bak name
	  Avoid that

