2011-02-08 21:18  gespinasse

	* lfs/glibc: Fix a minor random log noise due to racy ranlib test
	  That is not important as when test fail, ranlib is run without
	  need.
	  That change nothing except creating build log noise
	  
	  Remove wrong usage of --without-selinux on configure
	  There was a missing continuation character on previous line.
	  But as word started with -, --without-selinux was considered as a
	  command allowed to fail (and that fail).
	  
	  I have build on SE-linux enabled and non-SE-linux machine and I
	  haven't seen the need of --without-selinux
	  
	  The CFLAGS="$(CFLAGS)" on configure is very ugly, particulary
	  with first
	  CFLAGS =
	  and later
	  CFLAGS = -march=i486 -mtune=pentium -Os -pipe
	  -mno-tls-direct-seg-refs
	  I will try to clean that mess next.

