	  cleanup.
	  $LFS has no value in the chroot (after toolchain stage)

2011-01-20 07:15  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/gcc, config/rootfiles/common/stage2,
	  lfs/stage2: Cleanup gcc rootfile after openmp and mudflap removal
	  
	  During that, I find an error in stage2 where libgcc_s.so symlink
	  was create in /lib when the original file is installed in
	  /usr/lib.
	  Fix that and clean stage2 :
	  - mkinitramfs is installed in miscprogs
	  - /opt, var/opt are not used, dev is exclude in Config form the
	  path we search files
	  
	  We don't care that much if usr/lib/{libgcc_s.so*,libstdc++.so*}
	  are include in stage2 as they are later in gcc rootfile

2011-01-18 19:16  owes

	* updates/1.9.18/setup: Include modified upgrade.sh into update
	  package

2011-01-18 08:15  gespinasse

	* lfs/Config, lfs/initramfs, lfs/klibc, lfs/usb-key: Remove $LFS
	  variable when unneeded
	  $LFS is actually only defined in toolchain and is empty after as
	  we are in the chroot
	  Comment that in lfs/Config
	  
	  Add -n to gzip -f9 in usb-key, that will not hurt

2011-01-17 20:32  owes

	* src/scripts/upgrade.sh: Testing on running service will not work
	  when installing. Fixed.

2011-01-17 14:34  owes

	* lfs/linux: Update grsecurity patch

2011-01-17 06:25  gespinasse

	* lfs/gcc: We don't use openmp and mudflap, so disable
	  corresponding libs
	  That will reduce time for build and test, and reduce gcc errors
	  to 4 on 486 build

2011-01-16 21:54  gespinasse

	* lfs/ccache: Add a note to signal that we depend on how glibc is
	  compiled on host to run a dowloaded toolchain package on every
	  machines.
	  To compile a toolchain package we distribute, we should use an
	  host that does not require a recent kernel.
	  Debian v5 (lenny) require at least 2.6.8 , Ubuntu 10.04 require
	  2.6.15

2011-01-16 09:18  owes

	* lfs/linux: Update grsecurity patch

2011-01-16 07:44  gespinasse

	* lfs/e2fsprogs: I try to use --disable-debugfs but that cause
	  failure on tests, so not a good idea

2011-01-15 19:52  gespinasse

	* lfs/binutils, lfs/gcc, lfs/glibc, make.sh: I didn't like the
	  tautology in TARGET_TGT and try to find a better name.
	  TARGET_2 is not fabulous, but that's the target for pass2, so
	  good enought for me.
	  
	  When doing that change, I find my mystake when saving the
	  unhardened specs file. The target for pass2 should have been
	  used instead of LFS_TGT to run -dumpspecs. That should fix the
	  bunch of errors remaining after
	  GCC_TOLERATE_ALWAYS_OVERFLOW=1 fix
	  Tests are nNot yet finished for me but I am happy now with the 2
	  usuals error with unix/-fstack-protector
	  FAIL: gcc.c-torture/compile/limits-blockid.c -O0 (internal
	  compiler error)
	  FAIL: gcc.c-torture/compile/limits-blockid.c -O0 (test for excess
	  errors)
	  
	  I haven't yet added the supplementary hash with gcc specs

