2010-09-18 06:51  owes

	* config/ppp/ip-down, config/ppp/ip-up,
	  src/rc.d/rc.connectioncheck,
	  updates/1.9.16/ROOTFILES.i486-1.9.16: In some cases rc.updatered
	  takes several seconds to finish. pppd only waits 5 seconds,
	  before killin
	  g ip-down which can cause rc.connectioncheck not being started.
	  Running rc.updatered seperately and waiting for rc.updatered to
	  finish in rc.connectioncheck fixes it.
	  Add same procedure in ip-up.

