2010-04-26 23:23  gespinasse

	* config/install/init-mini-initramfs: And finally use xzminidec to
	  read floppy img and initramfs
	  We could handle that better in case floppy fail to read.
	  That happen frequently with bad and old media, dust ...

2010-04-26 23:14  gespinasse

	* lfs/initramfs: Mostly the end of this batch of changes
	  
	  Adjust initramfs build to use xz compressed floppy images
	  
	  Remove the acenic hack as there is now plenty enought places for
	  all nic drivers in 1 floppy
	  
	  Shift parted / libparted to root-2 floppy, this let 200 kB
	  compressed free on root-1.
	  (maybe go back to this but I didn't test)
	  
	  Use the macro to list files with size for mini-initramfs

2010-04-26 23:02  gespinasse

	* config/kernel/kernel.config.i486,
	  config/rootfiles/arch_i486/linux: Activate
	  CONFIG_OPTIMIZE_INLINING
	  This make the kernel a bit smaller
	  
	  Change some crypto code to be build as module, so vmlinuz is
	  smaller again.
	  This let us 33 kb free on floppy (with splash image include
	  again)
	  
	  Everything look to work for me, but this was more install-centric
	  than something else.

2010-04-26 22:57  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/xz-embedded, lfs/xz-embedded, make.sh:
	  Add zx-embedded
	  Now floppy root-1,root-2, scsi, network could be more efficiently
	  compressed
	  This let us a bit of confort in term of free space
	  (we could even keep strace on floppy)

2010-04-26 22:39  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/klibc, lfs/klibc: Change klibc
	  installation to be in the PATH
	  That way, we could compile xzminidec for floppy without troubles

2010-04-26 22:32  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/arch_i486/glibc, lfs/glibc: Add for remaining c
	  libs pulled by mklibs in initramfs
	  the corresponding _pic.a and _pic.map files
	  This reduce the installer by 22 kb (xz)compressed on root-1
	  
	  Update the rootfile and add corresponding _pic.{a,map}

2010-04-26 20:38  owes

	* lfs/linux, lfs/linux-headers: Upgrade kernel to 2.6.32.12

2010-04-26 20:23  gespinasse

	* lfs/newt: Use standard CFLAGS, not need for something special
	  
	  Set --prefix to /usr if a day we shift to shared lib
	  
	  Add comment how to use the shared lib and reduce with mklibs

2010-04-26 20:19  gespinasse

	* lfs/slang: Go back using standard CFLAGS, not need to use
	  something special.
	  
	  Comment how to use shared lib and reduce them with mklibs
	  Code is not smaller for the installer as only installer is
	  linked.
	  So only compile the static lib as before

2010-04-26 19:35  gespinasse

	* config/rootfiles/common/zlib, lfs/zlib: Add what was missing to
	  reduce zlib shared with mklibs
	  No more 'No pic file found ... copying'
	  Instead
	  /lib//libz.so.1 80003L
	  /installer/initramfs/lib/libz.so.1-so 70822L
	  /installer/initramfs/lib/libz.so.1-so-stripped 60428L
	  
	  No mandatory, but this should save 10 kb (before compression)
	  
	  Documentation say it is needed to compile the static lib with
	  -fPIC.
	  But as we compile with -fPIE, that look to be enought.

