2010-01-16 14:17  marcoson

	* html/html/images/blacklogo.png, html/vhost81,
	  html/vhost81/cgi-bin, html/vhost81/html,
	  html/vhost81/html/images, html/vhost81/html/images/blacklogo.png:
	  Squid and maybe some addons need to deliver content like images
	  via plain HTTP without SSL and/or authentication
	  
	  Therefore I've created a new virtual instance (vhost) of the
	  built-in web service listening on port 81. This new instance is
	  fully isolated from the existing part responsible for the admin
	  GUI.
	  
	  It has it's own DocumentRoot and it's own cgi-bin directory.

